queries.query: select count(*) as aggregate from (select `customers`.`id`, `customers`.`name`, `customers`.`phone`, `customers`.`email`, `customers`.`city`, `customers`.`address`, `customers`.`rating`, `customers`.`status`, `customers`.`updated_at`, `customers`.`vendor_id`, (select users.name from users where users.id = customers.vendor_id limit 1) vendor, (select count(*) from log_custs where customers.id = log_custs.customer_id) logs, (select count(*) from orders,clients,addresses where type_order = 0 and status in (5) and orders.client_id = clients.id and orders.address_id = addresses.id and addresses.phone = customers.phone) nbr_cmds, (select feedbacks.feed_product from orders,clients,addresses,feedbacks where feedbacks.order_id = orders.id and orders.type_order = 0 and orders.status in (5) and orders.client_id = clients.id and orders.address_id = addresses.id and addresses.phone = customers.phone limit 1) review, (select date(orders.created_at) from orders,clients,addresses where status in (3,5,8) and orders.client_id = clients.id and orders.address_id = addresses.id and addresses.phone = customers.phone order by orders.id desc limit 1) last_date_order, (select sum(if(items.price>0,items.quantity*items.price,0)) from orders,clients,addresses,items where items.order_id = orders.id and status in (5) and orders.client_id = clients.id and orders.address_id = addresses.id and addresses.phone = customers.phone) ca from `customers` where `customers`.`status` != ? and `customers`.`vendor_id` = ?) count_row_table
